<p><strong>Will It Fly? By Thomas McKnight PDF</strong></p>
<p><strong>What is "Will It Fly?" about?</strong></p>
<p>"Will It Fly?" is a children's book written by Thomas McKnight and illustrated by Teresa Murfin. It follows the story of Patty Paper, a young sheet of paper who dreams of flying. With the help of her friends, Patty sets out to discover if her dream is possible.</p>
<p><strong>What is the main theme of "Will It Fly?"</strong></p>
<p>The main theme of "Will It Fly?" is that anything is possible if you believe in yourself and never give up on your dreams. Patty Paper faces many challenges on her journey, but she never stops believing that she can fly.</p>
<p><strong>What are some of the questions that Patty Paper asks herself in "Will It Fly?"</strong></p>
<p>Throughout the story, Patty Paper asks herself several questions, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Can I really fly?</li>
<li>What will happen if I fail?</li>
<li>Should I give up on my dream?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>How does Patty Paper overcome her challenges in "Will It Fly?"</strong></p>
<p>Patty Paper overcomes her challenges with the help of her friends. She learns that it is important to have people who support you and encourage you to reach your goals. She also discovers that it is okay to ask for help when you need it.</p>
<p><strong>What is the ending of "Will It Fly?"</strong></p>
<p>In the end, Patty Paper is able to fly. She realizes that her dream is possible and that she never should have doubted herself. The story teaches children that anything is possible if they believe in themselves.</p>